WEBVTT

00:17.860 --> 00:18.820
CHAPTER XXX.

00:19.240 --> 00:23.120
The more I knew of the inmates of Morehouse, the better I liked them.

00:23.520 --> 00:29.900
In a few days I had so far recovered my health that I could sit up all day and walk out sometimes.

00:29.900 --> 00:36.680
I could join with Diana and Mary in all their occupations, converse with them as much as they wished,

00:37.140 --> 00:39.740
and aid them when and where they would allow me.

00:40.160 --> 00:46.260
There was a reviving pleasure in this intercourse, of a kind now tasted by me for the first time,

00:46.700 --> 00:52.300
the pleasure arising from perfect congeniality of tastes, sentiments, and principles.

00:53.360 --> 00:57.840
I liked to read what they liked to read. What they enjoyed delighted me.

00:57.840 --> 01:02.260
What they approved I reverenced. They loved their sequestered home.

01:02.820 --> 01:08.620
I, too, in the gray, small, antique structure, with its low roof, its lattice casements,

01:08.880 --> 01:16.060
its moldering walls, its avenue of aged furs, all grown a slant under the stress of mountain winds,

01:16.640 --> 01:22.520
its garden dark with yew and holly, and where no flowers but of the hardiest species would bloom,

01:22.980 --> 01:25.260
found a charm both potent and permanent.

01:26.060 --> 01:29.380
They clung to the purple moors behind and around their dwelling,

01:30.000 --> 01:34.600
to the hollow vale into which the pebbly bridle path leading from their gate descended,

01:35.060 --> 01:41.000
and which wound between fernbanks first and then amongst a few of the wildest little pasture fields

01:41.000 --> 01:46.980
that ever bordered a wilderness of heath, or gave sustenance to a flock of gray moorland sheep,

01:47.280 --> 01:53.140
with their little mossy-faced lambs. They clung to this scene, I say, with a perfect

01:53.140 --> 01:59.360
enthusiasm of attachment. I could comprehend the feeling and share both its strength and truth.

01:59.960 --> 02:05.220
I saw the fascination of the locality. I felt the consecration of its loneliness.

02:06.060 --> 02:12.480
My eye feasted on the outline of swell and sweep, on the wild coloring communicated to ridge and

02:12.480 --> 02:19.760
dell, by moss, by heathbell, by flower-sprinkled turf, by brilliant bracken and mellow granite

02:20.620 --> 02:27.580
These details were just to me what they were to them, so many pure and sweet sources of pleasure.

02:28.360 --> 02:34.360
The strong blast and the soft breeze, the rough and the halcyon day, the hours of sunrise and

02:34.360 --> 02:39.980
sunset, the moonlight and the clouded night, developed for me in these regions the same

02:39.980 --> 02:45.960
attraction as for them, wound round my faculties the same spell that entranced theirs.

02:47.660 --> 02:53.740
Indoors we agreed equally well. They were both more accomplished and better read than I was,

02:54.180 --> 02:58.540
but with eagerness I followed in the path of knowledge they had trodden before me.

02:58.980 --> 03:04.300
I devoured the books they lent me. Then it was full satisfaction to discuss with them in the

03:04.300 --> 03:10.200
evening what I had perused during the day. Thought fitted thought, opinion met opinion,

03:10.200 --> 03:13.020
we coincided, in short, perfectly.

03:14.240 --> 03:20.920
If in our trio there was a superior and a leader it was Diana. Physically she far excelled me,

03:20.980 --> 03:26.800
she was handsome, she was vigorous. In her animal spirits there was an affluence of life

03:26.800 --> 03:32.540
and certainty of flow, such as excited my wonder, while it baffled my comprehension.

03:33.080 --> 03:39.180
I could talk a while when the evening commenced, but the first gush of vivacity and fluency gone,

03:39.180 --> 03:46.160
I was feigned to sit on a stool at Diana's feet, to rest my head on her knee, and listen alternately

03:46.160 --> 03:52.900
to her and Mary, while they sounded thoroughly the topic on which I had but touched. Diana offered

03:52.900 --> 03:59.840
to teach me German. I liked to learn of her. I saw the part of instructress pleased and suited her,

04:00.300 --> 04:06.540
that of scholar pleased and suited me no less. Our natures dovetailed mutual affection of the

04:06.540 --> 04:12.600
strongest kind was the result. They discovered I could draw. Their pencils and color boxes were

04:12.600 --> 04:19.280
immediately at my service. My skill, greater in this one point than theirs, surprised and charmed

04:19.280 --> 04:25.560
them. Mary would sit and watch me by the hour together. Then she would take lessons, and a

04:25.560 --> 04:32.960
docile, intelligent, assiduous pupil she made. Thus occupied and mutually entertained, days passed

04:32.960 --> 04:41.100
like hours, and weeks like days. As to Mr. St. John, the intimacy which had arisen so naturally

04:41.100 --> 04:47.500
and rapidly between me and his sisters did not extend to him. One reason of the distance yet

04:47.500 --> 04:53.840
observed between us was that he was comparatively seldom at home. A large proportion of his time

04:53.840 --> 04:58.720
appeared devoted to visiting the sick and poor among the scattered population of his parish.

04:59.440 --> 05:05.100
No weather seemed to hinder him in these pastoral excursions. Rain or fair he would,

05:05.440 --> 05:11.200
when his hours of morning study were over, take his hat and, followed by his father's old pointer,

05:11.440 --> 05:17.900
Carlo, go out on his mission of love or duty. I scarcely know in which light he regarded it.

05:18.520 --> 05:24.400
Sometimes, when the day was very unfavorable, his sisters would expostulate. He would then

05:24.400 --> 05:30.700
with a peculiar smile, more solemn than cheerful. And if I let a gust of wind or a sprinkling of

05:30.700 --> 05:36.400
rain turn me aside from these easy tasks, what preparation would such sloth be for the future,

05:36.540 --> 05:42.760
I proposed to myself? Diana and Mary's general answer to this question was a sigh,

05:43.140 --> 05:49.380
and some minutes of apparently mournful meditation. But besides his frequent absences,

05:49.380 --> 05:54.680
there was another barrier to friendship with him. He seemed of a reserved and abstracted

05:54.680 --> 06:00.740
and even of a brooding nature. Zealous in his ministerial labors, blameless in his life and

06:00.740 --> 06:07.540
habits, he yet did not appear to enjoy that mental serenity, that inward content, which should be the

06:07.540 --> 06:13.560
reward of every sincere Christian and practical philanthropist. Often of an evening, when he sat

06:13.560 --> 06:19.840
the window, his desk and papers before him, he would cease reading or writing, rest his chin on

06:19.840 --> 06:26.160
his hand, and deliver himself up to I know not what course of thought, but that it was perturbed,

06:26.280 --> 06:30.960
and exciting might be seen in the frequent flash and changeful dilation of his eye.

06:31.920 --> 06:37.880
I think, moreover, that nature was not to him that treasury of delight that it was to his sisters.

06:37.880 --> 06:44.060
He expressed once, and but once in my hearing, a strong sense of the rugged charm of the hills,

06:44.480 --> 06:50.420
and an inborn affection for the dark roof and hoary walls he called his home. But there was more

06:50.420 --> 06:56.020
of gloom than pleasure in the tone and words in which the sentiment was manifested, and never did

06:56.020 --> 07:01.960
he seem to roam the moors for the sake of their soothing silence, never seek out or dwell upon the

07:01.960 --> 07:08.800
thousand peaceful delights they could yield. Incommunicative as he was, some time elapsed

07:08.800 --> 07:14.880
before I had an opportunity of gauging his mind. I first got an idea of its caliber when I heard

07:14.880 --> 07:21.360
him preach in his own church, at Morton. I wish I could describe that sermon, but it is past my

07:21.360 --> 07:28.900
power. I cannot even render faithfully the effect it produced on me. It began calm, and indeed,

07:28.900 --> 07:35.060
as far as delivery and pitch of voice went, it was calm to the end. An earnestly felt,

07:35.280 --> 07:40.500
yet strictly restrained zeal, breathed soon in the distant accents, and prompted the nervous

07:40.500 --> 07:46.860
language. This grew to force, compressed, condensed, controlled. The heart was thrilled,

07:46.900 --> 07:58.880
the mind astonished by the power of the preacher, neither was softened. Throughout there was a

07:58.880 --> 08:06.780
doctrine, election, predestination, reprobation were frequent, and each reference to these points

08:06.780 --> 08:12.980
sounded like a sentence pronounced for doom. When he had done, instead of feeling better, calmer,

08:13.120 --> 08:19.760
more enlightened by his discourse, I experienced an inexpressible sadness, for it seemed to me,

08:20.080 --> 08:25.240
I know not whether equally so to others, that the eloquence to which I had been listening

08:25.240 --> 08:31.760
had sprung from a depth where lay turbid dregs of disappointment, where move troubling impulses

08:31.760 --> 08:38.600
of insatiate yearnings and disquieting aspirations. I was sure St. John Rivers, pure-lived,

08:39.340 --> 08:46.160
conscientious, zealous as he was, had not yet found that peace of God which passeth all understanding.

08:46.580 --> 08:52.420
He had no more found it, I thought, than had I. With my concealed and wrecking regrets for my

08:52.420 --> 08:57.760
broken idol and lost Elysium, regrets to which I have latterly avoided referring,

08:58.160 --> 09:04.400
but which possessed me and tyrannized over me ruthlessly. Meantime a month was gone,

09:04.860 --> 09:09.920
Diana and Mary were soon to leave Morehouse, and return to the far different life and scene

09:09.920 --> 09:15.220
which awaited them, as governesses in a large fashionable south of England city,

09:15.680 --> 09:21.240
where each held a situation in families by whose wealthy and haughty members they were regarded

09:21.240 --> 09:27.200
only as humble dependents, and who neither knew nor sought one of their innate excellences,

09:27.620 --> 09:33.160
and appreciated only their acquired accomplishments, as they appreciated the skill of their cook,

09:33.580 --> 09:39.820
or the taste of their waiting-woman. Mr. St. John had said nothing to me yet about the employment

09:39.820 --> 09:45.540
he had promised to obtain for me, yet it became urgent that I should have a vocation of some kind.

09:46.320 --> 09:50.800
One morning, being left alone with him a few minutes in the parlour, I ventured to

09:50.800 --> 09:56.480
approach the window recess, which his table, chair, and desk consecrated as a kind of study,

09:56.920 --> 10:01.980
and I was going to speak, though not very well knowing in what words to frame my inquiry,

10:02.500 --> 10:08.260
for it is at all times difficult to break the ice of reserve glassing over such natures as his,

10:08.780 --> 10:12.460
when he saved me the trouble by being the first to commence a dialogue.

10:13.540 --> 10:18.000
Looking at me as I drew near, you have a question to ask of me, he said?

10:18.640 --> 10:23.740
Yes, I wish to know whether you have heard of any service I can offer myself to undertake.

10:24.920 --> 10:30.760
I found or devised something for you three weeks ago, but as you seemed both useful and happy here,

10:31.100 --> 10:36.660
as my sisters had evidently become attached to you, and your society gave them unusual pleasure,

10:37.160 --> 10:42.520
I deemed it inexpedient to break in on your mutual comfort, till their approaching departure

10:43.080 --> 10:45.180
should render yours necessary.

10:46.040 --> 10:48.720
And they will go in three days now, I said.

10:49.620 --> 10:53.220
Yes, and when they go, I shall return to the parsonage at Morton.

10:53.580 --> 10:56.980
Hannah will accompany me, and this old house will be shut up.

10:57.960 --> 11:02.540
I waited a few moments, expecting he would go on with the subject first broached,

11:02.720 --> 11:05.760
but he seemed to have entered another train of reflection.

11:06.260 --> 11:09.240
His look denoted abstraction from me and my business.

11:09.240 --> 11:13.140
I was obliged to recall him to a theme which was of necessity,

11:13.600 --> 11:16.160
one of close and anxious interest to me.

11:17.120 --> 11:19.740
What is the employment you had in view, Mr. Rivers?

11:20.260 --> 11:24.280
I hope this delay will not have increased the difficulty of securing it.

11:25.080 --> 11:30.400
Oh no, since it is an employment which depends only on me to give and you to accept.

11:31.640 --> 11:35.560
He again paused. There seemed a reluctance to continue.

11:35.560 --> 11:42.340
I grew impatient. A restless movement or two and an eager and exacting glance fastened on his face

11:42.340 --> 11:47.400
conveyed the feeling to him as effectually as words could have done, and with less trouble.

11:48.340 --> 11:52.620
You need be in no hurry to hear, he said. Let me frankly tell you,

11:52.860 --> 11:58.780
I have nothing eligible or profitable to suggest. Before I explain, recall, if you please,

11:59.240 --> 12:04.600
my notice clearly given that if I helped you it must be as the blind man would help the lame.

12:05.240 --> 12:08.800
I am poor, for I find that when I have paid my father's debts,

12:09.460 --> 12:15.080
all the patrimony remaining to me will be this crumbling grange, the row of scathed firs behind,

12:15.440 --> 12:21.300
and the patch of moorish soil with the yew trees and holly bushes in front. I am obscure.

12:22.020 --> 12:26.080
Rivers is an old name, but of the three sole descendants of the race,

12:26.200 --> 12:31.600
two earn the dependence crust among strangers, and the third considers himself an alien from

12:31.600 --> 12:38.620
his native country, not only for life but in death. Yes, and deems and is bound to deem himself

12:38.620 --> 12:44.940
honoured by the lot, and aspires but after the day when the cross of separation from fleshly ties

12:44.940 --> 12:50.460
shall be laid on his shoulders, and when the head of that church militant, of whose humblest

12:50.460 --> 12:58.260
members he is one, shall give the word, rise, follow me. Syngin said these words as he pronounced

12:58.260 --> 13:04.800
his sermons, with a quiet deep voice, with an unflushed cheek, and a coruscating radiance of

13:04.800 --> 13:13.700
glance. He resumed. And since I am myself poor and obscure, I can offer you but a service of poverty

13:13.700 --> 13:19.860
and obscurity. You may even think it degrading, for I see now your habits have been what the

13:19.860 --> 13:26.480
world calls refined, your tastes lean to the ideal, and your society has at least been amongst the

13:26.480 --> 13:33.440
educated. But I consider that no service degrades which can better our race. I hold that the more

13:33.440 --> 13:38.200
arid and unreclaimed the soil where the Christian labourer's task of tillage is appointed him,

13:38.520 --> 13:44.000
the scantier the mead his toil brings, the higher the honour. His, under such circumstances,

13:44.140 --> 13:49.260
is the destiny of the pioneer, and the first pioneers of the gospel were the apostles,

13:49.260 --> 13:52.360
their captain was Jesus, the Redeemer himself.

13:53.160 --> 14:01.180
Well, I said, as he again paused, proceed. He looked at me before he proceeded. Indeed,

14:01.320 --> 14:07.060
he seemed leisurely to read my face, as if its features and lines were characters on a page,

14:07.520 --> 14:12.860
the conclusions drawn from the scrutiny he partially expressed in his succeeding observations.

14:13.580 --> 14:19.360
I believe you will accept the post I offer you, said he, and hold it for a while, not permanently,

14:19.720 --> 14:25.760
though, any more than I could permanently keep the narrow and narrowing, the tranquil hidden office

14:25.760 --> 14:33.040
of English country incumbent, for in your nature is an alloy as detrimental to repose as that in mine,

14:33.220 --> 14:39.380
though of a different kind. Do explain, I urged, while he halted once again.

14:40.320 --> 14:46.880
I will, and you shall hear how poor the proposal is, how trivial, how cramping. I shall not stay

14:46.880 --> 14:53.160
long at Morton, now that my father is dead, and that I am my own master. I shall leave the place,

14:53.200 --> 14:58.920
probably in the course of a twelve month, but while I do stay, I will exert myself to the utmost for

14:58.920 --> 15:09.360
its improvement. Morton, when I came to it two years ago, had no school. The children of the

15:09.360 --> 15:15.840
one for boys, I mean now to open a second school for girls. I have hired a building for the purpose

15:15.840 --> 15:21.340
with a cottage of two rooms attached to it for the mistress's house. Her salary will be thirty

15:21.340 --> 15:27.300
pounds a year. Her house is already furnished, very simply, but sufficiently, by the kindness

15:27.300 --> 15:33.620
of a lady, Miss Oliver, the only daughter of the sole rich man in my parish, Mr. Oliver,

15:33.620 --> 15:39.860
the proprietor of a needle factory and iron foundry in the valley. The same lady pays for

15:39.860 --> 15:45.240
the education and clothing of an orphan from the workhouse, on condition that she shall aid the

15:45.240 --> 15:50.980
mistress in such menial offices connected with her own house and the school, as her occupation

15:50.980 --> 15:56.240
of teaching will prevent her having time to discharge in person. Will you be this mistress?

15:57.680 --> 16:03.260
He put the question rather hurriedly. He seemed half to expect an indignant, or at least a

16:03.260 --> 16:09.460
disdainful rejection of the offer, not knowing all my thoughts and feelings, though guessing some,

16:09.840 --> 16:15.540
he could not tell in what light the lot would appear to me. In truth it was humble, but then

16:15.540 --> 16:21.260
it was sheltered and I wanted a safe asylum. It was plodding, but then, compared with that of

16:21.260 --> 16:27.560
a governess in a rich house, it was independent. And the fear of servitude with strangers entered

16:27.560 --> 16:35.040
my soul like iron. It was not ignoble, not unworthy, not mentally degrading. I made my

16:35.040 --> 16:40.980
decision. I thank you for the proposal, Mr. Rivers, and I accept it with all my heart.

16:41.640 --> 16:47.960
But you comprehend me, he said. It is a village school. Your scholars will be only poor girls,

16:48.480 --> 16:54.080
cottagers' children at the best, farmers' daughters. Knitting, sewing, reading, writing,

16:54.080 --> 16:59.180
ciphering will be all you will have to teach. What will you do with your accomplishments?

16:59.880 --> 17:03.560
What with the largest portion of your mind, sentiments, tastes?

17:04.840 --> 17:11.040
Save them till they are wanted. They will keep. You know what you undertake, then? I do.

17:11.840 --> 17:18.300
He now smiled, not a bitter or a sad smile, but one well pleased and deeply gratified.

17:18.920 --> 17:21.740
And when will you commence the exercise of your function?

17:22.820 --> 17:27.540
I will go to my house tomorrow, and open the school, if you like, next week.

17:28.260 --> 17:35.200
Very well, so be it. He rose and walked through the room. Standing still, he again looked at me.

17:35.520 --> 17:42.300
He shook his head. What do you disapprove of, Mr. Rivers, I asked. You will not stay at Morton

17:42.300 --> 17:50.940
No, no. Why? What is your reason for saying so? I read it in your eye. It is not of that description

17:50.940 --> 17:56.640
which promises the maintenance of an even tenor in life. I am not ambitious.

17:57.960 --> 18:04.660
He started at the word ambitious. He repeated. No. What made you think of ambition? Who is

18:05.300 --> 18:11.000
I know I am. But how did you find it out? I was speaking of myself.

18:11.900 --> 18:20.080
Well, if you are not ambitious, you are. He paused. What? I was going to say impassioned,

18:20.360 --> 18:25.740
but perhaps you would have misunderstood the word and been displeased. I mean that human

18:25.740 --> 18:31.920
affections and sympathies have a most powerful hold on you. I am sure you cannot long be content

18:31.920 --> 18:36.880
to pass your leisure and solitude, and to devote your working hours to a monotonous labor

18:36.880 --> 18:42.300
wholly void of stimulus. Any more than I can be content, he added with emphasis.

18:43.060 --> 18:49.700
To live here buried in morass, pent in with mountain, my nature that God gave me contravened,

18:50.020 --> 18:56.400
my faculties heaven-bestowed, paralyzed, made useless. You hear now how I contradict myself,

18:56.560 --> 19:01.480
I who preached contentment with a humble lot, and justified the vocations even of

19:01.480 --> 19:08.620
wood and drawers of water in God's service. I, his ordained minister, almost rave in my restlessness.

19:09.380 --> 19:13.380
Well, propensities and principles must be reconciled by some means.

19:14.740 --> 19:20.360
He left the room. In this brief hour I had learned more of him than in the whole previous month,

19:20.720 --> 19:28.120
yet still he puzzled me. Diana and Mary Rivers became more sad and silent as the day approached

19:28.120 --> 19:33.880
leaving their brother in their home. They both tried to appear as usual, but the sorrow they

19:33.880 --> 19:40.000
had to struggle against was one that could not be entirely conquered or concealed. Diana intimated

19:40.000 --> 19:44.960
that this would be a different parting from any they had ever yet known. It would probably,

19:45.180 --> 19:50.820
as far as St. John was concerned, be a parting for years. It might be a parting for life.

19:51.580 --> 19:58.060
He will sacrifice all to his long-framed resolves, she said. Natural affection and feelings more

19:58.060 --> 20:04.760
potent still. St. John looks quiet, Jane, but he hides a fever in his vitals. You would think him

20:04.760 --> 20:10.800
gentle. Yet in some things he is inexorable as death, and the worst of it is my conscience will

20:10.800 --> 20:16.520
hardly permit me to dissuade him from his severe decision. Certainly I cannot for a moment blame

20:16.520 --> 20:23.420
him for it. It is right, noble, Christian, yet it breaks my heart. And the tears gushed to her

20:23.420 --> 20:30.640
fine eyes. Mary bent her head low over her work. We are now without father, we shall soon be without

20:30.640 --> 20:37.220
home and brother, she murmured. At that moment a little accident supervened which seemed decreed

20:37.220 --> 20:43.140
by fate, purposely to prove the truth of the adage that misfortunes never come singly,

20:43.140 --> 20:47.980
and to add to their distresses the vexing one of the slip between the cup and the lip.

20:48.860 --> 20:52.200
St. John passed the window reading a letter. He entered.

20:53.360 --> 20:59.600
Our uncle John is dead, said he. Both the sisters seemed struck, not shocked or appalled.

21:00.020 --> 21:03.380
The tidings appeared in their eyes rather momentous than afflicting.

21:04.260 --> 21:10.460
Dead, repeated Diana. Yes. She riveted a searching gaze on her brother's face,

21:10.460 --> 21:18.320
and what then, she demanded in a low voice. What then die, he replied, maintaining a marble

21:18.320 --> 21:26.620
immobility of feature. What then? Why, nothing. Read. He threw the letter into her lap. She

21:26.620 --> 21:32.160
glanced over it and handed it to Mary. Mary perused it in silence and returned it to her brother.

21:32.720 --> 21:38.140
All three looked at each other and all three smiled, a dreary pensive smile enough.

21:39.260 --> 21:42.600
Amen. We can yet live, said Diana at last.

21:43.440 --> 21:47.320
At any rate, it makes us no worse off than we were before, remarked Mary.

21:48.160 --> 21:53.520
Only it forces rather strongly on the mind the picture of what might have been, said Mr. Rivers,

21:53.940 --> 21:56.900
and contrasts it somewhat too vividly with what is.

21:57.800 --> 22:01.500
He folded the letter and locked it in his desk, and again went out.

22:02.240 --> 22:06.180
For some minutes no one spoke. Diana then turned to me.

22:06.740 --> 22:12.180
Jane, you will wonder at us and our mysteries, she said, and think us hard-hearted beings not

22:12.180 --> 22:17.220
to be more moved at the death of so near a relation as an uncle, but we have never seen

22:17.220 --> 22:23.640
him or known him. He was my mother's brother. My father and he quarrelled long ago. It was

22:23.640 --> 22:29.320
by his advice that my father risked most of his property in the speculation that ruined him.

22:29.900 --> 22:35.780
Mutual recrimination passed between them. They parted in anger and were never reconciled.

22:36.180 --> 22:42.540
My uncle engaged afterwards in more prosperous undertakings. It appears he realized a fortune of

22:42.540 --> 22:48.800
twenty thousand pounds. He was never married and had no near kindred but ourselves, and one other

22:48.800 --> 22:54.960
person, not more closely related than we. My father always cherished the idea that he would

22:54.960 --> 23:01.220
atone for his error by leaving his possessions to us. That letter informs us that he has bequeathed

23:01.220 --> 23:06.620
every penny to the other relation, with the exception of thirty guineas, to be divided

23:06.620 --> 23:13.600
between St. John, Diana, and Mary Rivers, for the purchase of three mourning rings. He had a right,

23:13.600 --> 23:19.900
of course, to do as he pleased, and yet a momentary damp is cast on the spirits by the receipt of such

23:19.900 --> 23:26.300
news. Mary and I would have esteemed ourself rich with a thousand pounds each, and to St. John such

23:26.300 --> 23:30.400
sum would have been valuable, for the good it would have enabled him to do.

23:31.640 --> 23:37.540
This explanation given the subject was dropped, and no further reference made to it, by either

23:37.540 --> 23:45.020
Mr. Rivers or his sisters. The next day I left Marsh End for Morton. The day after, Diana and

23:45.020 --> 23:50.760
Mary quitted it for distant be. In a week Mr. Rivers and Hannah repaired to the parsonage,

23:50.760 --> 23:53.560
and so the old grange was abandoned.

